{
  "title": "Introduction",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "level": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Introduction"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Alinea is an open source headless CMS written in Typescript. Its main highlights are:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "textAlign": "left",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Content is stored in flat files and can be committed to a git repository"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "textAlign": "left",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Content is bundled with deploys, meaning zero network overhead while retrieving content"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "textAlign": "left",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Content is fully typed when using Typescript"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Alinea comes packaged as a single library on NPM. It provides a CLI that lets you get going without setting up databases, environments, or any other services."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "0c3ZcIuX3S5DDMhK910DE",
      "type": "ChapterLinkBlock",
      "link": {
        "id": "pQQ6PFuITK3HiaihU-4ax",
        "type": "entry",
        "entry": "20580nQzbOBR3Lt4kIdxyRGglc6",
        "description": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Configuring the schema"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The content schema is configured in a central config file. Content types define different fields — Alinea ships with a lot of field types but can be expanded by creating custom fields."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ywilQqjnFgpesqZ88ztfg",
      "type": "CodeBlock",
      "code": "const BlogPost = alinea.type('Blog post', {\n  title: alinea.text('Blog entry title'),\n  path: alinea.path('Url path'),\n  body: alinea.richText('Body text')\n})",
      "fileName": "",
      "language": "",
      "compact": false
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "On a higher level content can be structured into "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "workspaces",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "data-id": "yMjicncya9hmF_nyXNIK_",
                "data-entry": "259EzPfnSUaKOrNL1S2bpIpMdKl",
                "data-type": null,
                "href": null,
                "title": null
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", which hold "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "roots",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "data-id": "2eukZ1z0XcPbzghBjKVAB",
                "data-entry": "28hcdyq0sGJdgY6kM24NZd1XP5S",
                "data-type": null,
                "href": null,
                "title": null
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". This allows you to separate websites, apps or other publishing channels into logical categories. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "UBTQRWVPpH2Lr6W2bnfhm",
      "type": "ChapterLinkBlock",
      "link": {
        "id": "rUUw37CkIwtQzLTqnDDPV",
        "type": "entry",
        "entry": "25HWCBHEFdsLDtooZ4mzxeax3An",
        "description": "Configuration"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Content structure"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Published content is formatted into JSON files, typically in a `/content` directory (we're "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "considering other formats",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "data-id": "cK3ZGUh6k2wYUjZdirQ8Y",
                "data-entry": null,
                "data-type": null,
                "href": "https://github.com/alineacms/alinea/issues/10",
                "target": "_blank",
                "title": null
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " as well). The JSON files are manually editable when needed. They can be checked into git, making it easy to collaborate."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Alinea indexes the JSON files into an embedded SQLite database. Having a database with indexed fields means querying content is fast and simple."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "Gs_7cGVP61b0kBG9DKV7u",
      "type": "ChapterLinkBlock",
      "link": {
        "id": "s1TBmqCylqtoDnUtpwZhI",
        "type": "entry",
        "entry": "28Ng6ZnpyhafrKdGMOO7BUUKP4S",
        "description": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Hosting the dashboard"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "While developing locally the Alinea CLI starts a server with the dashboard for you. Changes are written to the file system and can be committed to git manually during the development process. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "When your project is ready to deploy Alinea exposes a handler that can be hosted on most Javascript runtimes (Node.js or edge/serverless functions). The handler needs access to a backend service that can authenticate users, store drafts and publish changes back to the git repository. Alinea ships with some packages that help you build a backend — or one can be hosted via our "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "cloud service",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "data-id": "bj69FWaHNlyj1-7nXADBM",
                "data-entry": null,
                "data-type": null,
                "href": "https://www.alinea.cloud",
                "target": "_blank",
                "title": null
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "."
        }
      ]
    },
